Saudi Arabia's Interior Ministry spokesman listens to a question during a news conference in Riyadh
Stringer
Hugh Tomlinson
Last updated at 1:23PM, March 27 2013
A man was beheaded and his body then crucified in Saudi Arabia yesterday, the latest incident to provoke international condemnation of the conservative kingdom’s human rights record.
The Saudi Interior Ministry confirmed that Mohammed Hussein, a Yemeni man convicted of murder and sodomy, was put to death and his corpse put on public display in the southern city of Jizan.
